# ── App / run outputs ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Exported guides/connectors land here as STL; they are regenerable. But the
# SHIPPED assets under modules/ and input/ MUST be tracked (the app + the build
# need them), so re-include those two folders below.
*.stl
*.STL
# Re-include ONLY the shipped assets (whitelist). Everything else *.stl stays
# ignored — in particular the "* - CT.stl" scans in Input/ are NOT published.
!modules/
!modules/**
!Input/Demo_mandible.stl
!Input/Demo_fibula.stl

# ── Patient / CT-derived data, NOT for public release ───────────────────────
# The shipped demo uses the synthetic Demo_*.stl; the "* - CT.stl" scans and saved
# sessions look CT/patient-derived, so they are NOT published by default. Delete these
# lines (and re-add the files) only if you have confirmed the data is safe to share.
cases/
*_case.json
/Input/Mandible - CT.stl
/Input/Fibula - CT.stl
/Input/uniguide_session.json
/Input/uniguide_session_1.json

# ── Blender auto-backups ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.blend1

# ── PyInstaller build output (regenerable; GitHub Actions builds the release) ─
build/
dist/
*.manifest

# ── Interactive-debug scratch renders ───────────────────────────────────────
debug/

# ── Python ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ── Development-only utilities (not part of the release) ────────────────────
dev/

# ── Local tooling / editor / OS cruft ───────────────────────────────────────
.vscode/
.claude/
*.bak
desktop.ini
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
